<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1762] DateFormatTransformer does not work correctly with non-default locale dates</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1762</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The DateFormatTransformer assumes the default locale for date transformations. &lt;br/&gt;
If your computer or server has its language set to &apos;es&apos; and the input file has &quot;November 30, 2009&quot;, it&apos;ll throw an exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a reproducible test case:&lt;br/&gt;
Define an XML file:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;awardlist&amp;gt;&amp;lt;award&amp;gt;&amp;lt;expirationdate&amp;gt;November 30,  2009&amp;lt;/expirationdate&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/award&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/awardlist&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Define the data-config.xml with:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;field column=&quot;expirationdate_dt&quot; xpath=&quot;/awardslist/award/expirationdate&quot; dateTimeFormat=&quot;MMMMM dd, yyyy&quot;  /&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;ll throw:&lt;br/&gt;
Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.text.ParseException: Unparseable date: &quot;November 30, 2009&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Different locale in the imported data.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
